In cards with large images, the CSS `max-height` and `max-width` property are effectively overridden by the way AnkiDroid handles large images (see [here](https://github.com/ankidroid/Anki-Android/blob/c23cbff141e7ad9e5e5115a7b8a62169ee4ca05c/AnkiDroid/src/main/assets/card_template.html)). For example, if the card template specifies

    img {
      max-height: 120px;
    }

for a very large image, AnkiDroid's automatic image rescaling overrides `max-height`, setting the image width/height to whatever AnkiDroid's built-in maximum size is, rather than what the user specified. This happens even if 120px is *less* than the maximum height, potentially causing the final image to be taller than 120px.

Originally reported on Google Code with ID 1966
